You should also keep in mind that the Voodoo 3 can do a lot more effects than 
the Permedia 2. Some things as simple as mipmapping (which the Permedia can't 
do) and interpolated alpha, but also more blend modes.
In Heretic 2, for example, this will result in "real" fires (will look better 
than the emulated stuff on the Permedia), and colored lightmaps. If you ever 
saw the PC version, you'll know that the colored lightmaps do add a lot of 
atmosphere to the game. 

