Adding to what my brother already said, you might be aware that certain cards 
on the PC that feature Permedia2 chipsets (especially the high-end versions) 
do use the Permedia2 *exclusively* as a 2D chipset and have Glint/MX as 
renderer chips. The P2 is used as a framebuffer, nothing else.

So yes, you have to take the appropriate drivers in this case. Using the 
Permedia driver will not be very fast if you have to Glint/MX on the card :-)

Furthermore, compared to everything else currently in use, the Permedia2 
never runs optimally, since it is simply too slow

