> How hard is to code drivers for AGP gfx-cards ?...What do u think about
> supporting
> Matrox AGP gfx cards ?

AGP is just a PCI bus with another connector, and some minor modifications. 
You can use it in exactly the same way as a PCI connector, plus you can do 
some additional stuff with the AGP bus (like getting access to system 
memory). But the programming is exactly the same (just put stuff in 
registers).

As to Matrox cards, as these will be the cards for AmigaDE, there's no point 
in not supporting them with Warp3D. As we're already doing Voodoo 3 drivers, 
you can also plug in Voodoo boards. We will also look at other possibilities.

I would like to stress, though, that we're not going to support every board 
available. I've heard from some people that bought GeForce boards as soon as 
the PCI boards where released, expecting us to do drivers for these boards. I 
can only say to people that they should wait until the Warp3D team officially 
announces support for a board, before buying it.

> I was told that AmigaOne will be released at Q1 2000 (April/May, can we
> say?)..I thin
> AmigaOne1200PPC is a stable, better solution than Mediator or GREX ...

